# SomaliNotes AI Lecture Learning Platform | A Unified AI Framework for Somali Lecture Transcription, Translation, and Note Generation

## System Purpose, Goal, and Full Project Overview

This document explains what this project is about, why it was built, what problem it solves, and how the system works from the frontend pages to the backend processing pipeline.

The explanation is based on the current project files, folder structure, existing documentation, backend services, frontend pages, database models, and the AI prompt instructions embedded inside the code.

---

## Big Picture Purpose

- This project is a full-stack AI learning platform that turns lecture videos into structured Somali study notes.
- The main idea behind the system is to help Somali-speaking students learn from video lectures more easily.
- Instead of forcing a student to manually watch, pause, write, translate, and summarize a long lecture, the system automates that process.
- A user can submit a YouTube lecture link or upload a local lecture media file.
- The backend processes the media, extracts or obtains the spoken content, creates a transcript, and then uses AI to generate Somali educational notes.
- The final result is a learning dashboard where the student can read the transcript, study Somali notes, review summaries and key points, listen to notes, download notes, and ask a lecture chatbot questions and after all that he is examined with a quiz about the lecture.
- The project is also designed with an admin side so system managers can monitor users, lectures, jobs, logs, and processing health.

---

## Main Goal of the System

- The main goal is to convert educational lecture media into useful Somali learning materials.
- The system aims to support students who understand Somali better than English or who want lecture content explained in Somali.
- The platform reduces the time needed to prepare study notes from lectures.
- It makes video-based learning easier to review, search, organize, and reuse.
- It shows how AI can be applied in education, language support, speech-to-text processing, and student productivity.
- It provides a practical final-year-project system that combines frontend design, backend APIs, authentication, database management, media processing, AI transcription, AI note generation, and admin monitoring.

---

## Problem the Project Solves

- Many lectures are delivered as long videos, which are hard to revise from quickly.
- Students often need written notes, summaries, and key points, but creating them manually takes time.
- Somali-speaking learners may struggle when lecture content, transcripts, or explanations are mostly in English.
- YouTube lectures and uploaded videos are not automatically organized into a personal study library.
- Students may need to ask questions after a lecture, but they do not always have a tutor available.
- Admins need visibility into whether lecture processing jobs are succeeding, failing, or getting stuck.

This system solves these problems by automating lecture ingestion, transcription, Somali note generation, categorization, progress tracking, and lecture-based chatbot support.

