## Processing Pipeline Details

- The pipeline starts after a lecture is created.
- It uses clear stages so users and admins can see what is happening.
- It validates input before doing expensive work.
- It prepares source media from YouTube or upload.
- It downloads YouTube media for playback when needed.
- It checks captions first for YouTube videos because captions can save processing time.
- It extracts audio using FFmpeg when the system needs speech-to-text processing.
- It converts audio to a standard speech-friendly format.
- It splits long audio into chunks to avoid model and timeout limitations.
- It can process chunks in parallel.
- It has retry handling for temporary AI provider errors.
- It has fallback logic for difficult transcription cases.
- It records progress percent while the job is running.
- It writes logs for important events, warnings, and failures.
- It supports cancellation if the user cancels before processing completes.
- It saves successful results as transcript, notes, media metadata, and AI analysis.

